<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,225,403,429]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Betrem, 1928)" baseAuthorityName="Betrem" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[231,800,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Carinoscolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="vittifrons" subSpecies="hoozanensis">
<emphasis box="[231,625,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Carinoscolia vittifrons hoozanensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Betrem, J. G." box="[638,792,403,429]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="1 - 388" refId="ref13005" refString="Betrem, J. G. (1928) Monographie der Indo-Australischen Scoliiden mit zoogeographischen Betrachtungen. Treubia, 9 (Supplement), 1 - 388." type="journal article" year="1928">Betrem, 1928</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was once reported as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sichel, 1864)" baseAuthorityName="Sichel" baseAuthorityYear="1864" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Carinoscolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittifrons">
<emphasis box="[1213,1232,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1244,1344,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">vittifrons</emphasis>
(Sichel, 1864)
</taxonomicName>
. There are some minor differences, especially in colour between them (anterior part of T2 rather narrowly polished; upper part of area between antennal sockets and subvertex partially yellow in nominate 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sichel" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[1293,1429,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Carinoscolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittifrons">
<emphasis box="[1293,1429,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">C. vittifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, anterior part of T2 widely polished; upper part of area between antennal sockets up to posterior edge of head (sometimes excluding ocellar area) yellow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Tsuneki" authorityYear="1972" box="[663,832,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoozanensis">
<emphasis box="[663,832,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">C. hoozanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
